quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  17,85,"They question you concerning the Spirit. Say, ‘The Spirit is of the command of my Lord, and you have not been given of the knowledge except a few [of you].’"
  17,86,"If We wish, We would take away what We have revealed to you. Then you would not find for yourself any defender against Us"
  17,87,except a mercy from your Lord. Indeed His grace has been great upon you
  17,88,"Say, ‘Should all humans and jinn rally to bring the like of this Quran, they will not bring its like, even if they assisted one another.’"
  17,89,"We have certainly interspersed this Quran with every [kind of] parable for the people, but most people are only intent on ingratitude"
  17,90,"They say, ‘We will not believe you until you make a spring gush forth for us from the ground"
  17,91,Or until you have a garden of date palms and vines and you make streams gush through it
  17,92,"Or until you cause the sky to fall in fragments upon us, just as you have averred. Or until you bring Allah and the angels [right] in front of us"
  17,93,"Or until you have a house of gold, or you ascend into the sky. And we will not believe your ascension until you bring down for us a book that we may read.’ Say, ‘Immaculate is my Lord! Am I anything but a human apostle?!’"